						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment of a slab built into a wall of Gaṅgādharēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Tribhuvanamalla ?]</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record refers to the reign of a Chālukya king • • • • • <hi rend="bold">malladēva.</hi> The details of the date, etc., are lost. It mentions a gift to Kāḷōja, son of Bammōja who is called the <hi rend="italic">Sūtradhāri</hi> of God Svayaṁbhū.</p>						

